Description: Fragment of oval handle of a pottery transport amphora. Clay fine red-brown, very hard fired. Rectangular stamp. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) has four examples of this abbreviation. This piece does not appear to be of Rhodian origin, unlike the rest. Name Boethos
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1590)
